This paper deals with decision-making in uncertain environments with multiple agents, which is a common topic in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between exploration and exploitation, which is a key concept in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Bayesian methods and the consideration of uncertainty in the game environment suggest that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS).
